cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.RO 

This paper is about object detection in video using CNNs and temporal modeling. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes new CNN architectures for generating and classifying spatio-temporal tubes, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with video data, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of temporal modeling and object detection also suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. Finally, the paper's focus on object detection in video implies that it could also be relevant to cs.RO (Robotics).
